{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/posts/Upgrade-BlogEngineNET-from-25-to-26/","result":{"data":{"sitePage":{"id":"SitePage /posts/Upgrade-BlogEngineNET-from-25-to-26/"}},"pageContext":{"url":"/posts/Upgrade-BlogEngineNET-from-25-to-26/","relativePath":"posts/Upgrade-BlogEngineNET-from-25-to-26.md","relativeDir":"posts","base":"Upgrade-BlogEngineNET-from-25-to-26.md","name":"Upgrade-BlogEngineNET-from-25-to-26","frontmatter":{"title":"Upgrade BlogEngine.NET from 2.5 to 2.6","stackbit_url_path":"posts/Upgrade-BlogEngineNET-from-25-to-26","date":"2012-02-15 06:46:00","excerpt":"","comments_count":0,"positive_reactions_count":0,"tags":["BlogEngine.NET","upgrade","view count"],"canonical_url":"https://be-net.azurewebsites.net/post/2012/02/15/Upgrade-BlogEngineNET-from-25-to-26","template":"post"},"html":"<p>If you are running BlogEngine.NET 2.5, and you want to add post view count statistics feature to your webblog, then I recommend you apply this update to your blog installation.</p>\n<h1><span style=\"color: #800080;\">New feature: </span><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Post view count stats</span></h1>\n<p><strong>Front end screenshot:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Jeff-Tian/blogengine.net/master/Source/BlogEngine/BlogEngine.NET/App_Data/files/image_463.png\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 529px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 78.37837837837837%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block; transition: opacity 0.5s 0.5s; pointer-events: none;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Update BlogEngine.NET from 2.5 to 2.6\" title=\"Update BlogEngine.NET from 2.5 to 2.6\" src=\"/static/cc18444e5dc478ba3b1bb4c085f81b5a/67d6a/image_thumb_193.png\" srcset=\"/static/cc18444e5dc478ba3b1bb4c085f81b5a/12f09/image_thumb_193.png 148w,\n/static/cc18444e5dc478ba3b1bb4c085f81b5a/e4a3f/image_thumb_193.png 295w,\n/static/cc18444e5dc478ba3b1bb4c085f81b5a/67d6a/image_thumb_193.png 529w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 529px) 100vw, 529px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;opacity:0;transition:opacity 0.5s;color:inherit;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span></a>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Remark</em>: You can set the view count number appear next to the total number of comments.</p>\n<p><strong>Admin screenshot:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Jeff-Tian/blogengine.net/master/Source/BlogEngine/BlogEngine.NET/App_Data/files/image_464.png\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 536px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 51.35135135135135%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block; transition: opacity 0.5s 0.5s; pointer-events: none;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Update BlogEngine.NET from 2.5 to 2.6\" title=\"Update BlogEngine.NET from 2.5 to 2.6\" src=\"/static/471a4fe59108a94a710360d135d1d3f8/2d920/image_thumb_194.png\" srcset=\"/static/471a4fe59108a94a710360d135d1d3f8/12f09/image_thumb_194.png 148w,\n/static/471a4fe59108a94a710360d135d1d3f8/e4a3f/image_thumb_194.png 295w,\n/static/471a4fe59108a94a710360d135d1d3f8/2d920/image_thumb_194.png 536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 536px) 100vw, 536px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;opacity:0;transition:opacity 0.5s;color:inherit;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span></a></p>\n<p><em>Remark</em>: Via the extension manager, you can exclude the authenticated users as well as the specified IPs from accumulating the view count for a post.</p>\n<h1><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Changed file list:</span></h1>\n<pre>~\\DotNetSlave.BusinessLogic\\Post.cs\n~\\DotNetSlave.BusinessLogic\\Providers\\DbBlogProvider.cs\n~\\DotNetSlave.BusinessLogic\\Providers\\XmlProvider\\Posts.cs\n~\\BlogEngine.NET\\App_Code\\Extensions\\PostViewed.cs\n~\\BlogEngine.NET\\themes\\Standard\\PostView.ascx\n~\\BlogEngine.NET\\setup\\SQLite\\SQLiteUpgradeFrom2.5To2.6.txt\n~\\BlogEngine.NET\\setup\\SQL_CE\\SQL_CE_UpgradeFrom2.5to2.6.sql\n~\\BlogEngine.NET\\setup\\MySQL\\MySQLUpgradeFrom2.5To2.6.sql\n~\\BlogEngine.NET\\setup\\SQLServer\\MSSQLUpgradeFrom2.5to2.6.sql</pre>\n<h1><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Upgrade steps:</span></h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Always important! Backup your original blog;</li>\n<li>Download the upgrade zip file, and unzip it;</li>\n<li>Copy those files listed above in the unzipped folder to the corresponding folders of your blog installation place. For those files had already existed, replace them;</li>\n<li>Execute the repective sql statements if you are using a database. For example, if you are using SQLite for your blog, then execute the sql statements in the SQLiteUpgradeFrom2.5To2.6 txt. If you are not using a database (i.e. you are using xml as data storage for your blog), then you don’t need this step.</li>\n<li>Done.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><em>Reminder</em>: If you upgraded at the local machine, and then upload it to the remote server, remember upload the files under <em>bin</em> folder as well as other files. The safe way is uploading all files.</p>\n<h1><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Download:</span></h1>\n<p><a href=\"/blog/file.axd?file=2012%2f2%2fBE2.5To2.6.zip\">BE2.5To2.6.zip (321.98 kb)</a></p>","pages":[],"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Jeff Tian","author":"@zizhujy","description":"A wild full stack developer","palette":"yellow","header":{"title":"Jeff Tian","tagline":"A wild developer","logo_img":"https